overview: The user started by asking for help cleaning up their Vercel
  dashboard, which had five projects for the same
  application. I identified four duplicate projects and successfully deleted
  them using the Vercel CLI, leaving only the primary project. Following this,
  the user requested assistance in setting up a development environment. I
  recommended creating a  branch and leveraging Vercel's preview
  deployments and branch-specific environment variables. I created and pushed
  the  branch. During the environment variable setup, the user noticed
  that  was incorrectly set for the production
  environment. I promptly removed this variable from production and redeployed
  the production environment to ensure the change took effect. The final setup
  includes a clean Vercel dashboard with one main project, a  branch
  for preview deployments, and correctly scoped environment variables.
